6b45fc0f-e730-46db-88b9-56ff3e8133f0	16a62bc1-0a46-415c-a1e5-d1820dd26836	appearance	Deep gold to light amber in color. Bright to clear clarity. Large, creamy, persistent, white head.	{deep,white,amber,persistent,creamy,clear,head,bright,gold,light}	1	2025-09-27 21:25:58.475468+00
4d022973-ad9f-4613-a568-701bdb8a3391	16a62bc1-0a46-415c-a1e5-d1820dd26836	flavor	Moderately to moderately strong grainy-sweet, doughy, bready, or lightly toasty malt flavor dominates with some rich Maillard products providing added interest. Few caramel flavors optional. Low to moderate spicy, herbal, floral, pepperyhop flavor optional, but present in the best examples. Moderate hop bitterness, more so in the balance than in other Bocks. Clean fermentation profile. Well-attenuated, not cloying, with a moderately-dry finish that may taste of both malt and hops.	{moderately,herbal,hops,cloying,other,well,strong,optional,added,spicy}	1	2025-09-27 21:25:58.475468+00
fb5c63be-1e3a-427b-bb9b-67ee572758b2	16a62bc1-0a46-415c-a1e5-d1820dd26836	mouthfeel	Medium-bodied. Moderate to moderately-high carbonation. Smooth and clean with no harshness or astringency, despite the increased hop bitterness. Light alcohol warming optional.	{moderately,smooth,increased,carbonation,alcohol,with,high,moderate,light,harshness}	1	2025-09-27 21:25:58.475468+00
429aa322-314c-4a38-91e5-ef8985e0fef3	4bd1e402-877e-45c5-bed6-319008f72299	aroma	Moderately to moderately-high flowery, spicy, or herbal hops. Low to medium grainy, sweet, or doughy malt character, often with a light honey and toasted cracker quality. Clean fermentation profile. The hops should be forward, but not totally dominate the malt in the balance.	{moderately,often,herbal,hops,dominate,high,spicy,medium,grainy,flowery}	1	2025-09-27 21:25:58.475468+00
27ad2e36-17ef-48f8-86d6-3c878faf5dd0	4bd1e402-877e-45c5-bed6-319008f72299	appearance	Straw to deep yellow, brilliant to very clear, with a creamy, long-lasting white head.	{white,creamy,long,brilliant,clear,with,very,head,lasting,straw}	1	2025-09-27 21:25:58.475468+00
1334517b-a838-485c-8377-6e8913045745	4bd1e402-877e-45c5-bed6-319008f72299	flavor	Initial malt flavor quickly overcome with hop flavor and bitterness, leading into a dry, crisp finish. Malt and hop flavors similar to aroma (same descriptors and intensities). Medium to high bitterness, lingering into the aftertaste along with a touch of malt and hops. Clean fermentation profile. Minerally water can accentuate and lengthen the dry finish. Hops and malt can fade with age, but the beer should always have a bitter balance.	{hops,high,medium,lingering,flavors,aroma,touch,fade,always,same}	1	2025-09-27 21:25:58.475468+00
bf1eb0d8-e78d-47e0-acc7-1dc14295527e	4bd1e402-877e-45c5-bed6-319008f72299	mouthfeel	Medium-light body. Medium to high carbonation. Should not feel heavy. Not harsh, but may have a flinty, minerally, sharpness in some examples.	{body,some,harsh,flinty,carbonation,heavy,high,have,light,examples}	1	2025-09-27 21:25:58.475468+00
172c0392-6039-4665-b639-61cedbb6a142	8958f9cd-adfa-4f1c-91e6-53e708609140	aroma	Moderate malty aroma, typically rich, bready, somewhat toasty, with light bread crust notes. Clean lager fermentation character. Very lowfloral, herbal, or spicy hop aroma optional. Caramel-sweet, biscuity-dry, or roasted malt aromas are inappropriate. Very light alcohol might be detected, but should never be sharp. Clean, elegant malt richness should be the primary aroma.	{herbal,never,optional,spicy,might,crust,aroma,bread,caramel,elegant}	1	2025-09-27 21:25:58.475468+00
1307f3b1-6431-4f21-b685-6b2973b227d1	8958f9cd-adfa-4f1c-91e6-53e708609140	appearance	Amber-orange to deep reddish-copper color; should not be golden. Bright clarity, with persistent, off-white foam stand.	{white,amber,persistent,with,foam,color,bright,clarity,orange,copper}	1	2025-09-27 21:25:58.475468+00
606dfb56-d550-4cfc-8a23-6dc479b956bd	8958f9cd-adfa-4f1c-91e6-53e708609140	flavor	Moderate to highrich malt flavor often initially suggests sweetness, but the finish is moderately-dry to dry. Distinctive and complex maltiness often includes a bready, toasty aspect. Hop bitterness is moderate, and the floral, herbal, or spicy hop flavor is low to none. Hops provide sufficient balance that the malty palate and finish do not seem sweet. The aftertaste is malty, with the same elegant, rich malt flavors lingering. Noticeable sweet caramel, dry biscuit, or roasted flavors are inappropriate. Clean fermentation profile.	{often,moderately,herbal,hops,provide,none,initially,spicy,lingering,biscuit}	1	2025-09-27 21:25:58.475468+00
e7c5b1ff-5cd1-41f5-9eac-e6bce133928e	8958f9cd-adfa-4f1c-91e6-53e708609140	mouthfeel	Medium body, with a smooth, creamy texture that often suggests a fuller mouthfeel. Medium carbonation. Fully attenuated, without a sweet or cloying impression. May be slightly warming, but the strength should be relatively hidden.	{often,cloying,medium,without,fully,hidden,with,relatively,that,slightly}	1	2025-09-27 21:25:58.475468+00
b57c0011-a7cc-48ef-9f93-42de0b8c75f3	1fb54d20-6ce3-4706-aef9-844ceb22e08b	aroma	Blend of smoke and malt, varying in balance and intensity. The beechwood smoke character can range from subtle to fairly strong, and can seem smoky, woody, or bacon-like. The malt character can be low to moderate, and be somewhat rich, toasty, or malty-sweet. The malt and smoke components are often inversely proportional (i.e., when smoke increases, malt decreases, and vice versa). Low floral or spicy hop aroma optional. Clean fermentation profile.	{often,woody,inversely,strong,spicy,optional,subtle,seem,smoke,aroma}	1	2025-09-27 21:25:58.475468+00
ae2b54ef-ff93-4186-9f8a-8a195217e6fa	1fb54d20-6ce3-4706-aef9-844ceb22e08b	appearance	Very clear, with a large, creamy, rich, tan- to cream-colored head. Deep amber to coppery-brown in color, often a little darker than the underlying Märzen style.	{often,large,deep,colored,clear,with,head,little,color,very}	1	2025-09-27 21:25:58.475468+00
