edf53905-b143-4897-9abd-49aa1dfca65c	98e4e880-75f7-47dc-8c64-8f5253a23f18	aroma	Varies by base style. The fruit character should be noticeable in the aroma; however, some fruit (e.g., raspberries, cherries) have stronger aromas and are more distinctive than others (e.g., blueberries, strawberries) – allow for a range of fruit character and intensities from subtle to aggressive. Hop aroma may be lower than in the base style to better show the fruit character. The fruit should add an extra complexity, but not be so prominent as to unbalance the resulting presentation.	{stronger,raspberries,subtle,others,base,blueberries,cherries,aroma,distinctive,some}	1	2025-09-27 21:25:58.475468+00
